Friday afternoon and evening traffic heading west on I-70 can add 45-90 minutes to normal travel time. Denver residents leaving for weekend ski trips create bumper-to-bumper conditions from Morrison to Georgetown, particularly during ski season from December through April. I schedule my Friday deliveries before 2:00 PM to avoid this congestion entirely.

Sunday return traffic creates the opposite problem. Eastbound I-70 from the mountains back toward Denver experiences severe congestion from 2:00-8:00 PM as weekend visitors return home. While this doesn't directly affect Denver Airport to Breckenridge transportation, it does impact return scheduling for round-trip services.

Ski area opening and closing times influence traffic patterns in ways most people don't consider. Morning traffic to Breckenridge builds between 7:00-9:00 AM as day skiers arrive. Evening departures create congestion from 3:30-5:30 PM. Coordinating arrival and departure times to avoid these peaks improves travel experience significantly.

